===============================================================================
Parts List
===============================================================================
The following parts are just one way to cobble everything together using off
the shelf parts using protyping boards and such. You can, of course, use 
less expensive parts such as the Arduino Fio.

- Arduino Uno microcontroller board http://arduino.cc/en/Main/arduinoBoardUno
- BlinkM MaxM Ultrabright Smart LED (yes, these things are darn bright) 
  http://thingm.com/products/blinkm-maxm.html. This is just a starting point.
  Adventurous makers can experiment with traffic lights, light strips, etc.
- USB cable (TODO: type)
- Power Adapter (optionally you can try using power over ethernet if you
  are using Ethernet for communications)

If you plan on using Ethernet for communications:

- Arduino Ethernet Shield http://arduino.cc/en/Main/ArduinoEthernetShield
- Ethernet cable

If you plan on using Xbee for communications:
